I have completed the full implementation of the GrowEasy CRM AI-powered CSV Importer application based on the functional and technical requirements of your assessment.
Architectural Design Overview
To ensure the maximum security of your Gemini API key and maintain peak browser performance, this application is built on a Full-Stack (Vite + React + Express) architecture.
Intelligent Server-Side AI Mapper:
Uses the modern @google/genai SDK on the server, ensuring API keys are kept safe.
Leverages Gemini 3.5 Flash with custom systemInstructions and a rigorous JSON schema (responseSchema). This forces the model to reliably structure chaotic row keys (such as Ph. Number, Client Mail, Prospect) into validated CRM fields.
Progressive Batch Processing:
Instead of sending massive files in a single blocking request, the frontend segments rows into sequential batches (e.g., 10 rows per batch).
This enables real-time progress percentages, batch log readouts, and a recovery system where users can retry or skip failing batches.
Strict GrowEasy Business Compliance:
Enums: Automatically normalizes and maps incoming status keys to allowed status codes (GOOD_LEAD_FOLLOW_UP, DID_NOT_CONNECT, BAD_LEAD, SALE_DONE) and data sources.
Contact Consolidation: Extracts the first email and first phone number. Any supplementary emails or mobile numbers are appended as secondary records to the crm_note field.
Valid Record Check: Inspects each mapped record. If a row lacks both email and mobile numbers, it is safely skipped with a detailed reason returned to the user.
Core Functional Features

Steps to how to work our Application.

Step 1: Upload CSV & Sandbox Templates.
Drag-and-Drop Interaction: Includes an interactive file-upload area with visual drag-and-drop feedback and fallback manual file explorers.
Messy Sandbox Templates: To make testing seamless, we included three custom-styled realistic messy datasets (Facebook Lead Export, Marketing Agency Sheet, and Manual Excel Sheet) which contain dirty casing, missing rows, duplicate contact arrays, and custom headers. You can load any of these into the importer with 1-click.

Step 2: Raw Verification Table
Visual Grid: Renders the raw parsed rows in a responsive preview table with sticky headers, horizontal and vertical scroll wrappers, and empty value indicator badges.
No Premature AI Processing: Respects boundaries by keeping this step purely local and client-side until the user confirms.

Step 3: Active AI Processing Pipeline
Progress Diagnostics: Renders a loading display featuring a calculated percentage bar, live text readouts of active row mapping (e.g., "Mapping rows 11 to 20..."), and counters.
Interactive Error Recovery: If an API error or key issue occurs, the interface pauses, exposes the server logs, and provides a retry/skip menu to continue importing the remaining records.

Step 4: Mapped Lead Dashboard
Statistics Panel: Presents key metrics (Total Extracted, Skipped, and Total Imported) through clean visual counters.
CRM Lead List: Displays successfully formatted entries inside a beautiful, high-contrast table featuring colored pill status badges and source cards.
Search and Filter Rails: Includes a dynamic full-text search input and selector filters to isolate leads by CRM Status and Campaign Source.
Lead Inspector Panel: Clicking on any lead opens an inspector sidebar to review full coordinates, possession dates, and detailed CRM notes.
Skipped Records Logs: Offers a toggleable section mapping every skipped row number and its original CSV data with a clear reason (e.g., "Missing both email and mobile").
Multiple Exports: Enables downloading the mapped CRM database instantly in CRM CSV format or CRM JSON format.


